    "text": "FWIW, aside: what I see in this is something that Jef Raskin discussed in “The Humane Interface”. Measuring and increasing the size of the target area of buttons and selectable doo-dads. Now that I’m retired, I am discovering a lot of horrible UI problems in everything I use. I’ve had to disable cmd-Q in MacOS and ^X^C in emacs (due to increased finger-slop, I hit ^X and ^C together when I mean to hit only ^X). I regularly type cmd-C when I mean cmd-V only due to the physical closeness of those keys. I regularly click on the Claude icon in the dock when I mean to click on <http://draw.io|draw.io>, due to the similarity in background colour (orange) and the relative density of the foreground image (white splat for Claude vs. white node-and-wire for <http://draw.io|draw.io>, both filling about 75% of the icon, vs. the Pages icon which has an orange background but with only 30%-ish white foreground image). Disappearing and reappearing scroll bars and dock-bars are plain annoying. Auto-rearrangement of menu items (e.g. by recently used) is annoying and confusing - I first noticed this problem in SBCL’s restart menu (ultra-horrible UI, due to inconsistency).",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1761891896.324109",
    "parent_user_id": "UCUSW7WVD",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "pV6lr",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "FWIW, aside: what I see in this is something that Jef Raskin discussed in “The Humane Interface”. Measuring and increasing the size of the target area of buttons and selectable doo-dads. Now that I’m retired, I am discovering a lot of horrible UI problems in everything I use. I’ve had to disable cmd-Q in MacOS and ^X^C in emacs (due to increased finger-slop, I hit ^X and ^C together when I mean to hit only ^X). I regularly type cmd-C when I mean cmd-V only due to the physical closeness of those keys. I regularly click on the Claude icon in the dock when I mean to click on "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "http://draw.io",
                "text": "draw.io"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", due to the similarity in background colour (orange) and the relative density of the foreground image (white splat for Claude vs. white node-and-wire for "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "http://draw.io",
                "text": "draw.io"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", both filling about 75% of the icon, vs. the Pages icon which has an orange background but with only 30%-ish white foreground image). Disappearing and reappearing scroll bars and dock-bars are plain annoying. Auto-rearrangement of menu items (e.g. by recently used) is annoying and confusing - I first noticed this problem in SBCL’s restart menu (ultra-horrible UI, due to inconsistency)."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
